# Verification before shipping

- Before pushing or tagging (or when the user says they want to ship or release), run the project verify script so you have confidence in what is being shipped.
- From repo root: `./scripts/verify.sh` (or `bash scripts/verify.sh` on Windows). This runs the same checks CI runs: icon exists, GUI lint (ESLint), optional Python/tam-rfe smoke.
- If verify fails, fix the reported issues before suggesting a push or tag.
- In the GUI directory, `npm run lint` runs ESLint; fix any errors or warnings before considering the change complete.
